Operationalize externally built machine learning models by deploying them in Salesforce. 
Your business scientists can use their preferred modeling tools to design, build, test, and tune their models. You can’t deploy an externally built model in Hyperforce.

NOTE On August 1, 2024, you can no longer use externally built machine learning models in Einstein Discovery, and your prediction definitions that use an external model will fail. Instead, use Einstein Discovery to create a model.

Prepare an External Machine Learning Model to Upload
Set up your development environment to use the required software, then build an external model and prepare it for uploading.
Upload an External Machine Learning Model
Upload an externally built model that you’ve prepared. You can’t upload an externally built model in Hyperforce. Automated prediction writeback doesn’t support externally built models.
